==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Euxanthin
<hw>Eux*an"thin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>e'y^</grk> well + <?/ yellow.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A
yellow pigment imported from India and China. It has a strong odor, and
is said to be obtained from the urine of herbivorous animals when fed on
the mango. It consists if a magnesium salt of euxanthic acid. Called
also <altname>puri</altname>, <altname>purree</altname>, and
<altname>Indian yellow</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Euxenite</ent>⟦br⟧
